  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Change in Balance</measure>
    <time_frame>13 minutes</time_frame>
    <description>Balance was assessed during a 13-minute nocturnal light exposure (4 different conditions) and differences between the conditions were assessed. To determine goodness of balance while walking, the variability in stride length (i.e., variance in stride-to-stride length) was calculated in each of the conditions. Increased variability in stride length is associated with increased risk of falling.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
